The paper proposes a novel approach to model the Internet round trip time using a symbolic function network, which is a type of neural network model. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with network performance, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories.
